b:Common.ElementStruc.b:Text: Survey v2 Help File
The form content tree is where the building blocks of the form are put together. Drag fields from the right panel to the left panel to construct a form.
Clicking on a field will in most cases allow a dynamic preview of the contents.
The field selection panel is where you can find a selection of fields that can be dragged to the form content tree.
In the left column are block fields that form the structure of the form. The right column contains fields which determine the content and formatting for the form.
Left-drag within the left panel will move the field to a new position. Right-drag will copy the field instead.
This field sets the document properties, page size, and orientation.
Expand this field to set the page and form headers.
This field sets the header text at the top of each page.
This field sets the title header at the start of the document.
This field contains the sections that determine the form content.
This field contains the barcode at the bottom of each page.
This field contains the PDF preview of the form.
This field allows export of forms by subject name. In developer mode, help files can also be generated.
Sections together with their contents can be exported and later imported into other forms.
Sub-sections are repeating units whose contents are customised according to a list of tags.
This form item can be used to load MCQs from a Microsoft Excel file.
Blocks are basic structure units that contain content and formatting fields.
Insert this field to force a manual page break.
Use this field to insert a horizontal line divider.
Use this field to group related blocks together. This field does not affect the rendered form.
The border can surround the whole block, or a portion of the cells.
The background can surround the whole block, or a portion of the cells.
Automatic numbering for each block.
A text field. Contains elements that include formatting.
This field can be used to place images that have been loaded from a file.
Users can select one or more items from a list of horizontal choices.
Users can select one or more items from a list of vertical choices.
A choice field to select numbers. Only the tablets are used to determine the input.
A series of boxes for users to fill in characters. These may be numbers or alphanumeric entries.
A free entry field. The image is stored and the content must be processed manually.
Drag fields onto the recycle bin to remove them from the content tree.
Drag sections here to export them to a file.
Click these icons to switch to other modules. Drag items onto the help icon for more information.
The editing panel is for review of scanned marks and data entry.
This panel allows direct selection of the input field from the PDF preview.
The scanned image of the input field.
The input field with all detected marks. This can be changed by clicking on the displayed marks.
The left set of icons is for navigating between subjects. The right set of icons is for finding subjects with scanned data for review.
The left icon marks this subject as having been processed. The right icon hides marked subjects from view.
Load field definitions created by the common content module, or those saved by the scan module. Right clicking clears definitions.
Save field definitions.
Starts the scan process with the active scanner.
Selects the active scanner from a list of connected scanners.
Configures the active scanner.
Toggles between the table view for data entry and PDF view for direct selection of input fields.
Toggles between having no data filter, subjects with scanned data pending review, and subjects with scanned data.
Toggles between viewing detected marks (scanned), verified marks (manual data entry), and final marks (reconcile differences).
Save location for scanned images and exported files.
Should be set to high unless your computer is slow or has limited memory.
Turning this on reveals additional options for customisation. Most users should leave it off.
Load a new help file generated in developer mode by the common content module. Right click to save a template.
